<subSubSection id="95F4A2014833C192404034B9E20642DF" pageId="null" pageNumber="441" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="C5D5A62BDEE90672E598B22B5F477458" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">Westalpen-Flockenblume</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="C94F0EA474EE1B8E5093FE5FE937DCE1" pageId="null" pageNumber="441" type="description">
<paragraph id="78F5272B2934BB4DF7A0D6A9321A8163" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">
Unterscheidet sich von 
<taxonomicName id="0BB47723D7F2A30F064B86167E586115" class="Insecta" family="Calliphoridae" genus="Cyanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="null" pageNumber="441" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triumfettii">
<emphasis id="B9562247A43A9CB51FD2DE03592265D1" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">C. Triumfettii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 2b) durch folgende Merkmale: Bis 25 cm hoch; 
<emphasis id="04222D628A35C9280377AEB7D79BEF08" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">
<normalizedToken id="1A94F6976DF42949680127B7E40919FE" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
10
</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="3548C32BE021DF09CB50FDEFE3FBEA15" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">25mal so lang wie breit</emphasis>
, ziemlich dicht 
<normalizedToken id="7090DEF4FEF5648C01FB33D8CD6A3C38" originalValue="weißfilzig" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">weissfilzig</normalizedToken>
behaart, 
<emphasis id="64516BBE6F4503930A4AE631684000C0" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">
kaum am Stengel herablaufend; Fransen der mittleren 
<normalizedToken id="A818A96166872B9F05148DFD0ADA8F5D" originalValue="Hüllblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">Huellblaetter</normalizedToken>
2
</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="849C3150241DE1743E50BED5995208D9" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">4 mm lang.</emphasis>
- 
<normalizedToken id="4EFA5AD905586700DE5C86CBF0C6A2C6" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: 
<normalizedToken id="4D75BF6994E966C334423B5A30DA6967" originalValue="Später" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">Spaeter</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="9090A07F93C262438895AD2D87227C6C" originalValue="Frühling" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">Fruehling</normalizedToken>
und Sommer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DEB3C328FE9CDF210F9972C439440B4C" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">
<emphasis id="ABC22F33809FD2DCE0D43823ABEF5E53" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">Zytologische Angaben. 2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="1956226998DF1961D148C8290E0809B6" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">44:</emphasis>
Material aus den Alpes Maritimes (Guinochet 1957 1957a).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2777728BF5B656E4ACDDD23F2093003D" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">
<emphasis id="91108AD02E2581AF92D0455E4D519B54" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">Standort.</emphasis>
Subalpin. Wahrscheinlich 
<normalizedToken id="4A7B2C310EBD74E1282977C5DF07D69E" originalValue="ähnlich" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">aehnlich</normalizedToken>
wie 
<taxonomicName id="3BCE19B924D55940EA8238C2B7F1ED4B" class="Insecta" family="Calliphoridae" genus="Cyanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="null" pageNumber="441" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triumfettii">
<emphasis id="9BDFE4A40FEA659E2CAD586B53D53FD5" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">C. Triumfettii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 2b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="44221E0B668A74802DFD27373CAEE8ED" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">
<emphasis id="70C44E5CA91C30F44C49EDC059F2B0A7" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">Verbreitung. Westalpen-Pflanze:</emphasis>
Nach Guinochet (1957a) ist 
<taxonomicName id="A3B934ECD26128CC87DC6336ABE01D3F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Centaurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="441" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="seusana">
<emphasis id="CCA0FC539294E6AC6FF6B73415613902" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">C.seusana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
auch in andern 
<normalizedToken id="6AAC4263276452A71595DA0ED0614534" originalValue="südeuropäischen" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">suedeuropaeischen</normalizedToken>
Gebirgen und im Atlas verbreitet. - Angaben aus dem Gebiet beziehen sich wohl meist auf 
<taxonomicName id="18F50CF4104DFC52D19B4CC909B3F9FE" class="Insecta" family="Calliphoridae" genus="Cyanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="null" pageNumber="441" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triumfettii">
<emphasis id="D8DC06CF93FE9D7D8294E844EADB23B9" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="441">C. Triumfettii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 2b). Die Art kommt aber wahrscheinlich zwischen Cogne und Dondena im Aostatal vor (Vaccari 1904 bis 1911).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
